1
00:01:23,720 --> 00:01:24,519
Director Feng.

2
00:01:31,599 --> 00:01:33,279
Packing up and leaving so soon?

3
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:36,680
Yes.

4
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:37,800
I heard that

5
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:40,000
President Bai Pu of the China Lawyers Association

6
00:01:40,480 --> 00:01:41,319
will be taking over the legal team.

7
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:42,360
That's right.

8
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,680
He works very methodically.

9
00:01:44,959 --> 00:01:45,720
In my mind, he is

10
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:46,919
the perfect candidate for this position.

11
00:01:47,199 --> 00:01:48,000
Congratulations, then.

12
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:48,919
Thank you.

13
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:50,080
Out of courtesy,

14
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:51,360
I wish you all the best.

15
00:01:52,639 --> 00:01:54,080
But the road ahead of you is full of thorns.

16
00:01:54,639 --> 00:01:55,800
It doesn't look like an easy path.

17
00:01:57,559 --> 00:01:58,360
As for me,

18
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:00,360
I've never walked a smooth path anyway.

19
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,080
I'm already used to it.

20
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,120
Then watch your step.

21
00:02:04,959 --> 00:02:05,680
No need to see me out.

22
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,000
What a pity.

23
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:10,600
From now on, Director Feng won't be able to

24
00:02:10,600 --> 00:02:12,039
work with Lin Jiaqi every day.

25
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:14,679
Who knows?

26
00:02:15,399 --> 00:02:16,360
Once I leave the company,

27
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,479
does it mean we can't see each other?

28
00:02:18,360 --> 00:02:20,119
Jiaqi has her own ideas about her life.

29
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:22,039
She won't just follow your orders.

30
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:26,720
Don't be so full of yourself.

31
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:31,919
I should be the one saying that to you.

32
00:02:32,839 --> 00:02:33,960
I've been with Jiaqi

33
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,479
for at least ten years.

34
00:02:36,399 --> 00:02:37,639
I know her better than you do.

35
00:02:38,679 --> 00:02:40,559
That's not something you can just erase, President Gu.

36
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,559
I'll take my leave.

37
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:50,880
Come in.

38
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:55,320
President Gu.

39
00:02:55,559 --> 00:02:56,360
Here is the information

40
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,000
on the production manual you asked for.

41
00:02:58,199 --> 00:02:59,039
Also, at three o'clock,

42
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,759
you have a meeting with overseas investors.

43
00:03:01,279 --> 00:03:01,960
Got it.

44
00:03:03,160 --> 00:03:03,639
Have a seat.

45
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,039
Well...

46
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:12,559
What's wrong?

47
00:03:12,919 --> 00:03:14,839
Why are you the one

48
00:03:15,839 --> 00:03:16,759
accompanying me to the Tongzhou factory,

49
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,320
while the external trips

50
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,199
are handled by Qi Shuai?

51
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:20,800
That's because...

52
00:03:21,399 --> 00:03:21,839
Never mind.

53
00:03:22,559 --> 00:03:23,279
You can handle all of it.

54
00:03:23,279 --> 00:03:23,880
Me?

55
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:25,160
Also,

56
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:28,039
the report on economic trends,

57
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:30,520
Secretary Peng doesn't need to write it anymore.

58
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:31,720
You write it.

59
00:03:32,839 --> 00:03:33,720
And serving tea,

60
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,520
you'll do that too.

61
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:35,919
I have to serve tea too?

62
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:36,960
Yeah.

63
00:03:37,639 --> 00:03:38,199
Look,

64
00:03:38,399 --> 00:03:40,119
you know the preferences of external investors

65
00:03:40,279 --> 00:03:41,279
so well.

66
00:03:42,399 --> 00:03:43,399
I feel more at ease with you doing it.

67
00:03:44,399 --> 00:03:44,960
So,

68
00:03:45,279 --> 00:03:45,960
from now on,

69
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:48,119
all matters of Feimanchi, big and small,

70
00:03:48,119 --> 00:03:49,240
will be handed over to you.

71
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:51,399
You see,

72
00:03:51,559 --> 00:03:52,479
you work

73
00:03:52,679 --> 00:03:54,160
so proactively, diligently, and seriously.

74
00:03:54,679 --> 00:03:55,199
Therefore,

75
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:57,440
just take your time and do them one by one.

76
00:03:58,839 --> 00:03:59,559
I understand.

77
00:03:59,919 --> 00:04:00,440
That's all.

78
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,360
You can get back to work.

79
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,600
What's wrong with that monster?

80
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,759
He's making you do all the work alone.

81
00:04:11,759 --> 00:04:12,800
What are Shi Hui and I supposed to do?

82
00:04:12,839 --> 00:04:13,759
Cheer for you?

83
00:04:14,199 --> 00:04:15,080
How is that possible?

84
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,720
Who knows?

85
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:17,799
He suddenly said

86
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:18,959
I know everything like the back of my hand,

87
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,519
and handed all the work over to me.

88
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,839
Why on earth is he acting like this?

89
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,359
Lin Jiaqi,

90
00:04:24,559 --> 00:04:25,359
I want to control you.

91
00:04:25,559 --> 00:04:27,040
I won't let you escape my grasp.

92
00:04:27,239 --> 00:04:28,480
Is that what he said to you?

93
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:29,839
No.

94
00:04:30,279 --> 00:04:31,839
Maybe he'll assign work to you guys later.

95
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,040
Help me get the new product's

96
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,320
corporate updates.

97
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:36,799
Okay.

98
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,040
But,

99
00:04:40,359 --> 00:04:42,000
you're working way too hard now.

100
00:04:42,239 --> 00:04:43,760
And you're extremely serious.

101
00:04:43,959 --> 00:04:45,679
It's very different from before.

102
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,160
Really?

103
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,279
Sometimes,

104
00:04:49,679 --> 00:04:50,839
I feel like you treat President Gu

105
00:04:51,239 --> 00:04:52,000
just like an

106
00:04:52,279 --> 00:04:53,600
older sister in college

107
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:55,239
taking care of her grade-school brother.

108
00:04:55,839 --> 00:04:57,399
You help him with absolutely everything.

109
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,359
What are you talking about?

110
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,480
Just do your work.

111
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,079
I mean, tell me.

112
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,040
How can you be so petty?

113
00:05:14,359 --> 00:05:16,480
Just because she can't see your feelings,

114
00:05:16,679 --> 00:05:18,480
you boss her around to do everything?

115
00:05:19,079 --> 00:05:21,320
That's not very nice of you.

116
00:05:21,359 --> 00:05:22,959
I told you it's not like that.

117
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:23,920
Then what is it?

118
00:05:25,799 --> 00:05:26,720
With that brain of yours,

119
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,480
it'd be a miracle if you understood.

120
00:05:29,519 --> 00:05:31,040
I wanted to use work as an excuse

121
00:05:31,519 --> 00:05:32,959
just to see her a few more times.

122
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,359
I'm going crazy missing her.

123
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,640
But whenever she sees me, she only wants to talk about work.

124
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:45,079
Isn't that perfectly normal?

125
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,640
Think about it.

126
00:05:46,799 --> 00:05:48,839
Her boyfriend just passed away not long ago.

127
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:50,320
How could you possibly

128
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:52,000
win her heart so quickly?

129
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:57,519
Tell me, in this whole world,

130
00:05:57,519 --> 00:05:58,640
is there anyone else like me,

131
00:05:58,959 --> 00:06:00,920
in a love triangle with his own heart?

132
00:06:03,119 --> 00:06:03,760
Do you know

133
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:05,799
what's scarier than love?

134
00:06:06,959 --> 00:06:07,920
Memories.

135
00:06:08,239 --> 00:06:09,640
Memories.

136
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,119
Think about it.

137
00:06:11,279 --> 00:06:12,440
Jiaqi and her boyfriend

138
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:13,519
grew up together.

139
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:14,760
Can you ever beat

140
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,279
all those beautiful years they spent together?

141
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:17,760
Impossible.

142
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:18,679
Fortunately,

143
00:06:18,839 --> 00:06:20,320
President Gu, you and this Du Zheng

144
00:06:20,559 --> 00:06:22,440
have some similarities in behavior.

145
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:25,119
That's why she pays a bit more attention to you sometimes.

146
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:28,920
So you're saying

147
00:06:29,239 --> 00:06:31,200
every time Lin Jiaqi looks at me,

148
00:06:31,679 --> 00:06:33,079
she's thinking about another man?

149
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:35,079
Is she crazy?

150
00:06:35,880 --> 00:06:36,839
I'm going to find her right now

151
00:06:37,119 --> 00:06:37,640
and ask her clearly.

152
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,239
No, no, no.

153
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,000
President Gu.

154
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:39,720
I haven't finished speaking.

155
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:40,279
You haven't finished?

156
00:06:41,359 --> 00:06:42,079
In order to

157
00:06:42,679 --> 00:06:43,399
completely erase

158
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:44,000
the other man

159
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,359
from her heart,

160
00:06:46,559 --> 00:06:47,119
you

161
00:06:47,359 --> 00:06:49,399
should show off your charm.

162
00:06:51,559 --> 00:06:52,160
Then

163
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,000
how should I show off my charm?

164
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,519
Starting from now,

165
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:56,359
you

166
00:06:56,679 --> 00:06:58,000
need to start

167
00:06:58,799 --> 00:07:02,160
Operation Flirtation with Lin Jiaqi.

168
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:06,839
Operation

169
00:07:08,239 --> 00:07:09,040
Flirtation?

170
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:31,320
President Gu.

171
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:31,920
No, no, please.

172
00:07:32,399 --> 00:07:33,000
Stay seated.

173
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:36,920
What's wrong?

174
00:07:38,959 --> 00:07:40,799
I mean, I'm not here for anything specific.

175
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:42,239
You just keep doing your work.

176
00:07:52,519 --> 00:07:53,040
Is this

177
00:07:53,359 --> 00:07:54,559
our company's new product?

178
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,119
Yes.

179
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,040
It's a new product.

180
00:07:58,799 --> 00:07:59,640
It looks pretty good.

181
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,119
You don't need to look at me.

182
00:08:02,359 --> 00:08:03,079
Turn back around.

183
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:03,799
Just keep doing your work.

184
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:04,880
I'll just look around myself.

185
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,320
President Gu, what's wrong?

186
00:08:26,679 --> 00:08:28,600
I'm looking at this very important document.

187
00:08:32,599 --> 00:08:33,520
This isn't a document.

188
00:08:35,479 --> 00:08:37,239
It's the new menu for our company cafeteria.

189
00:08:40,359 --> 00:08:41,440
The menu is just as important.

190
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:43,200
Food is the most important thing.

191
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,320
I have to see what we're eating on Tuesday.

192
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,280
Tuesday is noodles with gravy.

193
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:50,440
That's my favorite.

194
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,359
Latest news.

195
00:08:56,359 --> 00:08:57,320
I heard Nelson...

196
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:59,280
...has already sold off the US real estate.

197
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,440
And invested it into new project development.

198
00:09:02,559 --> 00:09:03,359
So,

199
00:09:03,479 --> 00:09:04,679
Gu Tiancheng's assets...

200
00:09:04,679 --> 00:09:05,719
...must have hit rock bottom, right?

201
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:07,719
Then please give it another push.

202
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,280
Increase the scale of investment.

203
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:11,479
Leak some rumors in the stock market.

204
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,760
To shape public opinion.

205
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:14,559
I already released...

206
00:09:14,559 --> 00:09:15,960
...news about the overseas investment project today.

207
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:20,159
I reckon right now...

208
00:09:20,479 --> 00:09:21,760
...he doesn't even know his own future.

209
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,640
He's probably just running around aimlessly.

210
00:09:24,039 --> 00:09:25,000
Dai Sanyi.

211
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,520
What are you doing?

212
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,320
How did it go?

213
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:30,599
Did you succeed?

214
00:09:30,799 --> 00:09:32,039
You have the nerve to ask.

215
00:09:32,359 --> 00:09:33,239
What a lousy method.

216
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,280
It sucked.

217
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:37,239
No way.

218
00:09:37,640 --> 00:09:38,840
It works every time for me.

219
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,640
I get the feeling you're talking about.

220
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,599
But there's no way to start with her.

221
00:09:43,239 --> 00:09:45,159
What do you mean "no way to start"?

222
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:47,080
No, what was the situation?

223
00:09:49,479 --> 00:09:50,039
Look.

224
00:09:50,359 --> 00:09:51,359
She's sitting right here, right?

225
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:53,719
You naturally go around behind her.

226
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:54,239
Right?

227
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,719
Jiaqi, what are you doing?

228
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:56,599
Then lean in this way.

229
00:09:56,599 --> 00:09:57,599
Then roll up your sleeves, right?

230
00:09:57,599 --> 00:09:58,080
Yeah.

231
00:09:58,119 --> 00:09:58,840
The hand, you can't...

232
00:09:59,119 --> 00:09:59,599
Stop fooling around.

233
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,599
What's wrong with your sleeves?

234
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:03,960
I was planning to do this.

235
00:10:04,080 --> 00:10:04,559
But...

236
00:10:23,599 --> 00:10:24,400
Just sign here, right?

237
00:10:24,559 --> 00:10:24,919
Right.

238
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:31,679
I'm so touched by your story.

239
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:34,440
Hello?

240
00:10:36,359 --> 00:10:37,200
What do you mean, where am I?

241
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,359
I'm already up here.

242
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,080
Why did you go to the parking lot?

243
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,559
Come find me immediately.

244
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,039
Right now, immediately.

245
00:10:47,359 --> 00:10:47,919
Gu Tiancheng.

246
00:10:50,479 --> 00:10:52,080
Aren't you that female cop?

247
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,280
It's me.

248
00:10:54,679 --> 00:10:55,400
Give me the phone.

249
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:56,239
What for?

250
00:10:57,159 --> 00:10:58,080
Give me the phone.

251
00:10:58,599 --> 00:10:59,840
Are you robbing me?

252
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,520
Not this one.

253
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:06,119
Why is the ringtone the same?

254
00:11:09,159 --> 00:11:09,840
Can I go now?

255
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:27,200
Is it because...

256
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:29,080
...that phone's ringtone...

257
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,679
...is the same as mine...

258
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,119
...that you're acting like this?

259
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:35,679
What "this" or "that"?

260
00:11:36,039 --> 00:11:37,119
Which phone are you talking about?

261
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:39,599
The phone from the night Du Zheng was murdered.

262
00:11:40,359 --> 00:11:41,520
How do you know that?

263
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,479
Did that phone go missing?

264
00:11:45,640 --> 00:11:47,200
And it was taken by someone, right?

265
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:50,640
Who exactly are you?

266
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:51,400
Come clean.

267
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,000
It hurts, you know?

268
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:53,640
Let go.

269
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:54,400
I won't let go.

270
00:11:55,239 --> 00:11:56,320
Why do you know so much?

271
00:11:56,599 --> 00:11:57,440
How do you know about that phone?

272
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,039
Speak!

273
00:11:58,359 --> 00:11:59,440
This is my company.

274
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,760
Believe it or not, I'll call for help.

275
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:03,640
Fine.

276
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:04,960
Fine.

277
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,440
I guess you don't know

278
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:11,200
about my relationship with Jiaqi and Du Zheng.

279
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:12,359
What?

280
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:13,919
The three of us,

281
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,000
and Feng Ziang.

282
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:18,760
The three of us

283
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:20,520
all grew up together.

284
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,159
As for Brother Du's case,

285
00:12:22,280 --> 00:12:23,200
both professionally and personally,

286
00:12:23,760 --> 00:12:24,960
I will investigate it to the end.

287
00:12:25,559 --> 00:12:26,640
Now you know.

288
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,880
Someone like you,

289
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,799
all brawn and no brains.

290
00:12:30,119 --> 00:12:31,159
Cut the crap, kid.

291
00:12:32,479 --> 00:12:33,159
Let me ask you,

292
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,640
why are you so interested

293
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,520
in this case?

294
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,880
How did you find out?

295
00:12:37,799 --> 00:12:38,400
As a

296
00:12:38,400 --> 00:12:39,559
dignified Chief Executive Officer,

297
00:12:39,919 --> 00:12:41,119
why are you investigating this case?

298
00:12:42,119 --> 00:12:42,840
Want to know?

299
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:44,479
Yes.

300
00:12:45,039 --> 00:12:45,960
Why should I tell you?

301
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:47,679
Stop right there!

302
00:12:49,239 --> 00:12:49,640
Let go!

303
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,400
- Let go! - No!

304
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:51,359
I won't let go!

305
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:54,919
You!

306
00:12:55,039 --> 00:12:55,440
Let go!

307
00:12:55,599 --> 00:12:56,599
Let go! Let go of President Gu!

308
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:57,359
What are you yelling for?

309
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,239
Come help me!

310
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:01,760
What are you doing?

311
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,640
Let's talk in the office.

312
00:13:04,719 --> 00:13:05,400
Does it hurt here?

313
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,239
Of course it hurts!

314
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,479
What are you doing?

315
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:12,679
You have so much strength,

316
00:13:12,679 --> 00:13:13,719
why don't you go catch criminals?

317
00:13:13,919 --> 00:13:15,239
You're hurting us innocent civilians.

318
00:13:15,239 --> 00:13:16,080
What are you doing?

319
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,280
Are you done?

320
00:13:19,359 --> 00:13:20,200
Done for now.

321
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:23,640
Let me ask you,

322
00:13:24,359 --> 00:13:25,640
about Du Zheng's missing phone,

323
00:13:25,799 --> 00:13:26,479
how did you know?

324
00:13:27,239 --> 00:13:29,080
You just said someone took it.

325
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,400
How do you know someone took it,

326
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,159
and not something else?

327
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:33,599
I guessed.

328
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:35,719
Besides,

329
00:13:36,119 --> 00:13:37,359
if the phone is gone,

330
00:13:38,679 --> 00:13:40,000
it could only have been taken by someone.

331
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:41,280
What else?

332
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:43,000
Did the phone grow legs and walk away?

333
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:45,599
Fine.

334
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,119
Let me ask you again,

335
00:13:48,239 --> 00:13:49,679
why are you investigating this case?

336
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,159
What does it have to do with you?

337
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:54,080
I thought Lin Jiaqi was so pitiful.

338
00:13:55,359 --> 00:13:57,159
Facing such a thing all alone,

339
00:13:58,039 --> 00:13:59,479
so I wanted to show her some care.

340
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,080
As a boss caring for a subordinate,

341
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,000
tell me, Officer,

342
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:06,559
is there a problem?

343
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,679
I thought you were acting out of a guilty conscience.

344
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,520
Why would I have a guilty conscience?

345
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:12,640
Of course you don't know.

346
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:14,000
Du Zheng's death is indirectly related to you.

347
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,679
What did you say?

348
00:14:17,359 --> 00:14:18,919
After the Feimanchi substandard materials incident

349
00:14:18,919 --> 00:14:19,479
came to light,

350
00:14:19,479 --> 00:14:20,280
everyone

351
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:22,080
thought you were the mastermind behind it.

352
00:14:22,080 --> 00:14:22,960
Including Du Zheng.

353
00:14:23,919 --> 00:14:25,200
He didn't want to see his father

354
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,440
and Jiaqi overwhelmed,

355
00:14:27,239 --> 00:14:28,359
so he investigated privately.

356
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,280
And then something happened to him.

357
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:33,359
You kid,

358
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,559
if you hadn't been hospitalized at the time,

359
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:36,719
you would be a suspect.

360
00:14:36,719 --> 00:14:37,840
You definitely wouldn't be cleared of suspicion.

361
00:14:37,840 --> 00:14:38,479
Do you know that?

362
00:14:40,239 --> 00:14:41,039
No, well,

363
00:14:41,919 --> 00:14:42,599
Officer Ma'am,

364
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,520
sit down and calm down first.

365
00:14:43,520 --> 00:14:44,159
I won't calm down.

366
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,359
Then listen to me.

367
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,200
How could our President Gu

368
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,320
possibly be a suspect?

369
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:51,280
Think about it,

370
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,280
if he were the killer,

371
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:53,400
how could he

372
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:54,880
tell you about the missing phone?

373
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,760
How could he secretly send someone to investigate?

374
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,159
Would he catch himself?

375
00:14:58,400 --> 00:14:59,679
Does he have nothing better to do?

376
00:15:10,479 --> 00:15:11,760
You older guys are so ridiculous.

377
00:15:11,919 --> 00:15:12,640
At your age,

378
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:13,960
you still think you're young studs.

379
00:15:14,479 --> 00:15:15,359
Calling everyone "auntie".

380
00:15:15,799 --> 00:15:16,760
What a bad habit.

381
00:15:22,559 --> 00:15:23,119
Come in.

382
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:24,280
President Gu.

383
00:15:30,719 --> 00:15:31,280
Jiaqi.

384
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:32,440
Yao Yao.

385
00:15:32,919 --> 00:15:33,880
Why are you here?

386
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:46,559
I don't mean to criticize you,

387
00:15:46,719 --> 00:15:47,799
but you're going too far.

388
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:48,880
As soon as you arrive at our company,

389
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:50,200
you start making trouble without a word.

390
00:15:51,919 --> 00:15:53,440
This is really a bit of a misunderstanding.

391
00:15:53,919 --> 00:15:54,640
I didn't want to either.

392
00:15:56,239 --> 00:15:57,679
What's going on with your company lately?

393
00:15:58,159 --> 00:15:59,280
I haven't seen you for a while,

394
00:15:59,679 --> 00:16:00,640
and suddenly that guy

395
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:01,440
became the Chief Executive Officer?

396
00:16:02,679 --> 00:16:03,880
It happened not long ago.

397
00:16:05,359 --> 00:16:06,359
What gives him the right?

398
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,640
I always feel like he's very unreliable.

399
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,919
Always doing things so secretively.

400
00:16:11,119 --> 00:16:12,760
And somehow knowing so much inside information.

401
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,479
What is his actual goal?

402
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,080
To save the company,

403
00:16:16,599 --> 00:16:17,599
he's been running around everywhere,

404
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:18,880
working himself to the bone.

405
00:16:19,799 --> 00:16:21,080
He's even lost a lot of weight.

406
00:16:21,719 --> 00:16:23,080
I was just feeling frustrated

407
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:24,599
that I couldn't help him.

408
00:16:25,599 --> 00:16:26,320
And here you are,

409
00:16:26,559 --> 00:16:27,559
causing more trouble for me.

410
00:16:27,719 --> 00:16:28,960
You're really embarrassing me.

411
00:16:29,640 --> 00:16:30,159
You...

412
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:31,960
What are you talking about?

413
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:33,559
Why do I feel like suddenly

414
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:34,520
I don't even know you anymore?

415
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:36,840
What's wrong with me?

416
00:16:37,239 --> 00:16:38,919
Didn't you always say he was a bad guy?

417
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:40,919
Always saying he was causing trouble in the company,

418
00:16:41,159 --> 00:16:42,359
and deliberately making things difficult for you?

419
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:43,280
You made it sound like

420
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,880
the two of you were completely at odds.

421
00:16:45,599 --> 00:16:46,440
What's with you today?

422
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,080
Suddenly saying he's pitiful.

423
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:49,559
What on earth are you saying?

424
00:16:50,039 --> 00:16:51,119
I'm just stating the facts.

425
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,280
Telling it like it is.

426
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:54,440
No.

427
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,880
Don't tell me you've fallen for that guy?

428
00:16:59,559 --> 00:17:00,440
Don't talk nonsense.

429
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,320
How is that possible?

430
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,079
Although I'm not...

431
00:17:05,479 --> 00:17:06,719
not that petty of a person,

432
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:07,920
and it's none of my business,

433
00:17:08,439 --> 00:17:09,160
but...

434
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,400
to tell you the truth,

435
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:14,520
Du Zheng hasn't been dead

436
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:15,920
on that cold ground for very long.

437
00:17:16,239 --> 00:17:17,160
Why do I feel like

438
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:18,800
you've forgotten him so quickly?

439
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:20,520
Having a new romance,

440
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:21,760
having a new life.

441
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,640
I really feel sorry for Du Zheng.

442
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:26,280
And on top of that, it's that guy.

443
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:27,719
That makes me even sadder.

444
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:29,719
Stop talking nonsense.

445
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:31,599
That's not true at all.

446
00:17:32,839 --> 00:17:33,800
This is my duty.

447
00:17:34,199 --> 00:17:35,160
To think of my boss,

448
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:35,800
and manage everything.

449
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:36,599
It's perfectly normal.

450
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:38,359
If

451
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:39,439
that's not the case,

452
00:17:39,439 --> 00:17:40,680
then that's truly a relief.

453
00:17:41,079 --> 00:17:42,160
But Jiaqi,

454
00:17:42,839 --> 00:17:44,359
are you really not using work as an excuse

455
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:45,359
to deceive yourself?

456
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,520
And towards that Gu Tiancheng,

457
00:17:49,760 --> 00:17:50,599
do you really not have

458
00:17:51,239 --> 00:17:52,119
any other feelings?

459
00:17:57,520 --> 00:17:58,199
Ziang.

460
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,239
You called me over in such a hurry.

461
00:18:00,839 --> 00:18:02,439
Are you in some kind of trouble?

462
00:18:03,119 --> 00:18:04,400
Is there anything I can help you with?

463
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:05,760
Dad.

464
00:18:06,239 --> 00:18:07,239
What trouble could I possibly be in?

465
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:09,359
I just want

466
00:18:09,800 --> 00:18:11,079
you to move in with me.

467
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:12,959
Live together?

468
00:18:13,439 --> 00:18:14,959
Because I've been quite busy with work lately.

469
00:18:15,359 --> 00:18:16,599
I have a lot of things to handle.

470
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:18,959
I'm worried I won't be able to look after you.

471
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:20,680
If you move in here,

472
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:22,280
wouldn't it be much more convenient?

473
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:24,800
All right.

474
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:26,479
I understand.

475
00:18:27,079 --> 00:18:28,000
After I go back,

476
00:18:28,079 --> 00:18:29,000
I'll resign right away.

477
00:18:33,839 --> 00:18:34,479
That guy Feng.

478
00:18:36,839 --> 00:18:37,400
Uncle Feng.

479
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:38,560
Hello.

480
00:18:40,359 --> 00:18:41,599
I just called Ziang that

481
00:18:41,959 --> 00:18:43,079
as a joke.

482
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,040
Please don't mind it.

483
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:45,280
I don't.

484
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:47,199
What are you doing here?

485
00:18:47,719 --> 00:18:48,520
What's the matter?

486
00:18:48,959 --> 00:18:49,760
I came to see you.

487
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:50,959
Of course it's about something.

488
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:53,199
And it's something very important.

489
00:18:53,760 --> 00:18:54,640
Let's talk another day.

490
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:56,520
My dad is here today.

491
00:18:57,199 --> 00:18:57,800
I'm very busy.

492
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,359
What if I say it's about the substandard materials incident?

493
00:19:02,719 --> 00:19:04,359
Would you have something to say to me then?

494
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:09,199
Why bring this up again?

495
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:11,199
Isn't this matter already over?

496
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,760
Our partnership has also ended.

497
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,000
Why mention it?

498
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:16,880
I want to know,

499
00:19:17,599 --> 00:19:18,880
the person who did the dirty work for you back then,

500
00:19:19,719 --> 00:19:20,439
was it Tan Feng?

501
00:19:20,959 --> 00:19:22,079
Is there any point in bringing up the past?

502
00:19:22,959 --> 00:19:24,319
You asked me to get this done.

503
00:19:24,839 --> 00:19:26,119
I just needed to do it well.

504
00:19:26,959 --> 00:19:27,520
As for

505
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:28,680
who executed it in the process,

506
00:19:29,199 --> 00:19:30,199
and where each step went,

507
00:19:30,599 --> 00:19:31,520
do I need to report to you?

508
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:34,199
What exactly did Tan Feng do for you?

509
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:35,599
Just say what you want to say.

510
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:36,839
Don't beat around the bush.

511
00:19:37,719 --> 00:19:39,800
Could it be that after receiving your orders,

512
00:19:41,520 --> 00:19:42,560
Tan Feng also killed someone for you?

513
00:19:43,199 --> 00:19:44,199
What the hell are you talking about?

514
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:47,640
I heard from Officer Lin

515
00:19:48,599 --> 00:19:50,199
that Du Zheng was investigating

516
00:19:50,199 --> 00:19:51,479
the substandard materials incident.

517
00:19:52,040 --> 00:19:53,280
And he had gathered clues.

518
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,599
Then he suddenly died in an accident.

519
00:19:56,079 --> 00:19:57,000
You know about this, right?

520
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,000
I guess that's how it was.

521
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:01,439
So what?

522
00:20:02,319 --> 00:20:04,040
"I guess that's how it was"?

523
00:20:04,599 --> 00:20:06,079
Didn't you ask me because you didn't know?

524
00:20:06,439 --> 00:20:07,800
Why are you saying you guess so now?

525
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:09,719
Could it be that

526
00:20:10,520 --> 00:20:11,800
you and Tan Feng together,

527
00:20:12,239 --> 00:20:12,839
worried that

528
00:20:13,479 --> 00:20:15,239
Du Zheng would expose the truth about you,

529
00:20:15,599 --> 00:20:16,319
so you

530
00:20:16,439 --> 00:20:17,479
killed to silence him?

531
00:20:18,439 --> 00:20:20,000
What nonsense are you spouting in broad daylight?

532
00:20:21,199 --> 00:20:22,839
Even the police don't solve cases like you do.

533
00:20:23,599 --> 00:20:25,199
I don't need to say anything more to you here.

534
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:26,680
If you really want to know,

535
00:20:27,119 --> 00:20:28,040
wait until Tan Feng wakes up

536
00:20:28,439 --> 00:20:29,400
and ask him yourself.

537
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,599
You probably don't know yet.

538
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:32,640
Tan Feng has already woken up.

539
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,000
And I guess in a day or two,

540
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,839
he'll be able to speak.

541
00:20:37,599 --> 00:20:38,439
But I guess

542
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,079
Tan Feng probably won't tell

543
00:20:40,079 --> 00:20:41,439
the truth to the police.

544
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:42,880
Moreover,

545
00:20:43,439 --> 00:20:44,400
he'll try hard to help you

546
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,040
cover up what you've done.

547
00:20:46,680 --> 00:20:47,359
So,

548
00:20:48,319 --> 00:20:50,239
I'm going to make all of this public.

549
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:51,839
Let everyone know

550
00:20:52,079 --> 00:20:53,599
that the mastermind behind Du Zheng's death

551
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,079
is you.

552
00:20:56,239 --> 00:20:56,920
What do you want?

553
00:20:58,239 --> 00:20:59,880
Are you threatening me with this?

554
00:21:00,839 --> 00:21:01,479
Do you have any evidence?

555
00:21:02,119 --> 00:21:03,839
Du Zheng was your best friend.

556
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,800
You could even lay a hand on your best friend.

557
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:09,199
Now I'm really starting to worry

558
00:21:09,199 --> 00:21:10,160
about Lin Jiaqi's safety.

559
00:21:10,359 --> 00:21:11,520
Watch your mouth.

560
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:14,119
There's a limit to being overly paranoid.

561
00:21:14,959 --> 00:21:15,560
These words,

562
00:21:15,839 --> 00:21:16,599
you can't just say them recklessly.

563
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:18,040
I actually hope all of this

564
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:19,280
is just my over-paranoia.

565
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:21,439
Otherwise,

566
00:21:23,079 --> 00:21:24,719
Lin Jiaqi's life would be too pitiful.

567
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:27,280
But don't worry.

568
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,760
To protect Lin Jiaqi's safety,

569
00:21:30,479 --> 00:21:32,280
I will fight you to the bitter end.

570
00:21:33,719 --> 00:21:34,560
Let's wait and see.
